(1) The Council shall consist of— (a) the Chief Justice; (b) a Judge of the Supreme Court or High Court Judge nominated by the Chief Justice; (c) the Attorney-General, the Solicitor-General and the Director of Public Prosecutions; (d) two legal practitioners nominated by the Law Society of Zambia and appointed by the Minister; (e) two members of the academic staff of the School of Law of the University of Zambia nominated by the Vice-Chancellor of the University on the recommendation of the School and appointed by the Minister; and (f) the General Editor of the Zambia Law Reports appointed under section six if he is not a member by virtue of any of the preceding paragraphs.
