(1) Subject to subsection (2), there shall be paid out the funds of the Council — (a) to the members of the Council and members of the Editorial Board who are not also members of the Council , allowances to cover expenses reasonably incurred by them in respect of their attendance at meetings of the Council or the Editorial Board but not otherwise; (b) to the General Editor, an honorarium of such amount as the Council may determine in addition to any allowances payable under paragraph (a); (c) to the reporters appointed by the Council , such fees as the Council may determine; and (d) to staff appointed by the Council , such salaries as it may determine.
